rComments: Such a gem, the best prof I had in uni. So so so caring! She gave us 15% free just for writing 2 questions. Quizzes were ok if you studied a little before hand, and she took the 4 out of 6 best assignments. Would take her again in a heartbeat!

Dr. D'Ambrosio is easily one of the best professors in this entire university. Extremely caring about the success and well being of her students. Will take every chance to help students understand. Other profs should learn from her!
If you have the chance to take her online do it. 4 assignments, each 25%, best 3/4. Course content was super interesting and organized. She answers emails immediately and is really nice.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Graded by few things', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Best professor I've ever had. She genuinely cares about her students and takes the time to remember them by name. She went back to teacher's collage to teach better for her students after she started teaching at UO! She is very fair when it comes to tests. She gives you the tools to succeed. There arent enough characters to describe her awesomeness

Dr. D'Ambrosio was easily one of the best profs I've ever had. She was a breath of fresh air during these online classes and it really felt as though she cared about her students during the pandemic. Her expectations were always very clear, and although there was a lot of content, everything was graded very generously. Please take her classes!!!

FAV! Most caring prof I've seen, responds to all emails, has the best brightspace page, best slides, clear grading criteria, very reasonable expectations. She's really nice! she let me take the course while taking the prerequisite. 4 15% assignments, 40% final. I LOVE HER. I can't wait to take other courses w/ her. Wish other profs were like her.

One word: Amazing. Take any class she teaches. Her slides are amazing but does require you to read them over and memorize (she highlights important topics or things that don't need memorization). Always got grades back extremely fast and she's super caring.

Immunology is an information dense class but Lisa is a great teacher. You can tell she wants everyone to succeed. Her exams are a mix of multiple choice, T/F and long answers. The exams are extremely fair if you study for them. The application questions require that you think so be prepared for that. All in all, I recommend any of her classes.

rComments: Amazing professor! The class had potential to be very boring but she present he material so well. Her slides are so organized and clear if you miss a lecture its more than fine. She is open to giving advice about grad school and is so caring. I would recommend any class taught by Lisa
She's very passionate and conscious as a professor. You can tell she really cares about her students.

Lisa is AMAZING! Her lectures are very detailed and she is very clear on her expectations for the exams. Go to the exam review sessions because they will save your life. She is a very generous marker and is willing to listen to your opinions on her marking scheme for the midterms and finals. The quizzes are also an easy way to boost your grade up.

She is a absolute gem, she really wants her students to succeed. Her slides are so clear and well organized, and she explains everything very clearly. I also had her for Immunology and Virology and she's consistently a really great prof. Her tests are challenging but fair, she prepares you well for them via her practice problems amd review lectures

Very resilient to give you any marks on midterms/finals for remarking. Be lucky if she gives you a 0.25 of a point , even though you said the right thing but not in her keywords. Her keywords will give you 0.5 off every question, if you don't match it exactly. Even if there is an another answer to a question unlikely togrant you marks. Hard marker!

rComments: She is honestly amazing, she does her best to write fair exams and makes sure you understand what she is teaching. She does reviews and puts questions at the end of every lecture as a study tool. She is very nice and will gladly write you a letter of recommendation if she gets to know you.

AN ANGEL! Best prof ever. Her slides detail EVERYTHING you need to know and are so beautifully designed and clear. Her tests are fair, but studying for them does require a decent amount of effort (as any 4th year science class would). She is so helpful and had 2 review classes for our exam. Also, final is not cumulative so that's a bonus. LOVE HER.

Her slides are amazing! But beware because virology is taught by 3 profs in total. The midterms and final are all very fair but differ a bit based on the prof. Lisa is such a gem, she gives amazing lectures and is super clear with what she expects from her students. Would recommend all the MIC courses with her!
Amazing prof! Take all of her classes!

Lisa is amazing! She is so sweet and genuinely wants her students to succeed. Lectures are content-heavy but if you give yourself enough time to study her tests are very fair. Love her so much. She is also willing to give you feedback on grad school research proposals and write letters of recommendation if she gets to know you.
Really great professor, slides are clear and concise and reflective of what you need to know. Really cares about here students!

Lisa is the bomb . com! Her lecture slides are just as beautiful as she is. Everything you need to know is written on the slides, so it's very easy to follow in class. Her midterms are a mixture of MCQs, matching, and short answer questions (extremely fair if you put in the effort).

The best science prof I have ever had! The most beautiful PowerPoints and ultra clear grading criteria. It's a fourth year science class, so be prepared to learn a TON of information, but Lisa tries to make it as easy as possible and she cares about her students so much

Probably the best notes I've ever seen, especially considering it's a fourth year class. Amazing lecturer, gives you all the details you need to know and really good at explaining any other difficult concepts. Wish she'd taught the whole course, instead of some other profs coming in
